            "answer_text": "How to write a leave letter due to fever. This is a sample draft sick leave application for your references. Sample 1 (office) (Date) To, The HR Manager (company name) (Place) Subject: Sick leave application for a day. Respected Sir/Ma'am, I would like to apply for a leave tomorrow i.e. xx-xx-xxxx (date) as I am down with high fever / cold / stomachache / headache / viral infection. The doctor has advised me to take bed rest for a day. I am enclosing doctor's note for your perusal and record. Please contact me on my personal phone if you have any important doubts or queries about the current project. Thanking in anticipation. Sincerely, (Your name) (ID No.) (Your job position) (Company name)  Sample 2 (school) (Date) To, The Principal/Headmaster/Class Teacher (School name and address) Subject: Application for leave of absence. Sir/ma'am, I am (your name), student of class (Your class and division). With due respect, I would like to inform you that I will not be able to attend school tomorrow, ie xx-xx-xxxx, due to high fever / cold / stomachache / headache / viral infection. The doctor has advised me to take bed rest for a day. I am enclosing doctor's note for your perusal and record. Therefore, I request you to kindly grant me a leave of absence for those days. Thanking you. Yours obediently (Your name) Class - (standard and division) Roll No: (your roll no.)  I hope this answer is helpful to you. Thank you. ",
